{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 XML documents are basically just formatted text files. There is no "database manager" or indexing. \par
\par
However, they can work similarly to a heirarchical database, and Magic mimics that behavior by creating "views" into the XML document. Each view shows one level of repeating elements.\par
\par
You can then either work with these records individually, or in subforms, just as you would any other Data source.\par
\par
In this example, each of the Address Book XML views are shown individually. You can also view the raw XML using the "View Raw XML" button.\par
}
